# Adamenko Photography — environment variables
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, and set the same keys in the Vercel project
# (Production + Preview). None of these are committed (.env / *.local are gitignored).
#
# The placeholder values below are ILLUSTRATIVE — replace each `<…>` with a real
# value. The code reads every value from the environment; there are NO production
# values hardcoded anywhere, so wiring this up after buying a domain is config-only
# (no code change). Full walkthrough: docs/email-architecture.md.

# ── Site origin (SEO) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute origin used for canonical URLs, OpenGraph/Twitter URLs, sitemap, robots
# and JSON-LD. MUST be the real production origin or every canonical/OG URL breaks.
# No trailing slash. Falls back to http://localhost:3000 in dev if unset.
# Launch can run on the Vercel subdomain; switch to the custom domain by editing
# this one var (no code change).
#   e.g. https://adamenko-photography.vercel.app   (or https://adamenko-photography.fr)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://<your-domain-or-vercel-subdomain>

# ── Contact form delivery (Resend) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The /api/contact route posts to the Resend REST API. Until ALL THREE are set the
# route returns 503 and the form shows a graceful error with the email/Instagram
# fallback — it never fails silently and never blocks the build.
#
# After buying the production domain, the entire setup is:
#   1. resend.com → create account + API key            → RESEND_API_KEY
#   2. Resend → Domains → add + verify your domain (SPF/DKIM/DMARC DNS records)
#   3. set CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL to an address ON that verified domain
#   4. set CONTACT_TO_EMAIL to the inbox that should receive inquiries
#   5. add these three vars in Vercel (Production + Preview) → redeploy → test send
# DNS records + checklist: docs/email-architecture.md.

# 1. Resend API key (https://resend.com → API Keys).
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# 2. Where inquiries are delivered — the photographer's real inbox. Any working
#    address (a Gmail is fine); it does NOT need to be on the verified domain.
CONTACT_TO_EMAIL=<inbox-that-receives-inquiries>

# 3. The From address. MUST be on a domain you have verified in Resend
#    (e.g. bonjour@adamenko-photography.fr). Do NOT use a resend.dev address in
#    production — the route logs a warning if you do.
CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL=contact@<your-verified-domain>

# ── Google reviews sync (scripts/sync-reviews.mjs) ────────────────────────────
# Used ONLY by `npm run sync:reviews` (locally, or by the scheduled GitHub Action
# via repository secrets of the same names) — never read by the site at runtime
# or at build. Full setup + cost notes: docs/google-reviews.md.
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=<google-cloud-api-key-with-places-api-new>
GOOGLE_PLACE_ID=<the-business-place-id>
